COMP2404A — Assignment 1 (HomeShare CRUD)

Name: Mohamed Azab
Student Number: 101331588

------------------------------------------------------------
Overview
------------------------------------------------------------
This assignment implements a simple backend system for a HomeShare-style
reservation manager (similar to Airbnb). The system supports adding/removing
rentals, adding/removing reservations, and printing rentals/reservations.
All data is stored using statically allocated arrays (no dynamic memory).

The program is tested using the provided Tester class and the menu in main.cc.


------------------------------------------------------------
Included Files
------------------------------------------------------------

Provided:
- main.cc
  Runs the automated test menu used for marking.
- Tester.h / Tester.cc
  Test suite utilities (output capture + checks).
- Category.h / Category.cc
  Category enum and categoryToString() helper function.
- defs.h
  Contains MAX_ARRAY constant.

Implemented by me:
- Date.h / Date.cc
  Date class updated for this assignment. Added equals() and lessThan().
  Also includes the required month-name bug fix from the assignment update.
- Reservation.h / Reservation.cc
  Stores reservation info (name, number of people, check-in/out dates).
- Rental.h / Rental.cc
  Stores rental info and manages reservations for one rental unit.
  Reservations are stored sorted by date with no overlaps.
- HomeShare.h / HomeShare.cc
  Main manager class that stores rentals and supports CRUD operations.

Build:
- Makefile
  Compiles all code and produces the executable: a1


------------------------------------------------------------
Compilation Instructions
------------------------------------------------------------
To compile:

  make clean
  make


------------------------------------------------------------
Execution Instructions
------------------------------------------------------------
To run:

  ./a1

Then select one of the menu options (1–6).
Option 6 runs all automated tests and displays the total score.


